  <span id="freeText838590754812902736" style="display:none">I was skeptical when I picked this up, but was rewarded in the end. Magical realism isn't my thing so when Shelby started receiving anonymous letters I was thinking, 'oh no, letters from beyond?' I was too hooked by that point to care. Shelby is dealing with a death of a friend that she feels responsible for and withdraws form everyone. Enter a friend, a few dogs, and endless Chinese food. The healing power of dogs really can soften a character so full of angst and guilt. I enjoyed this coming of age story as Shelby finds forgiveness, acceptance, and her calling.</span>
